SIMPLE: overwhelm
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overwhelm
<hw>O`ver*whelm"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Overwhelmed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Overwhelming</conjf>.]</vmorph>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To cover over completely, as by a great wave; to
overflow and bury beneath; to ingulf; hence, figuratively, to immerse
and bear down; to overpower; to crush; to bury; to oppress, etc.,
overpoweringly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sea <qex>overwhelmed</qex> their enemies.</q> <rj><qau>Ps.
lxxviii. 53.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fearfulness and trembling are come upon me, and horror hath
<qex>overwhelmed</qex> me.</q> <rj><qau>Ps. lv. 5.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Foul deeds will rise,⟦br⟧
Though all the earth <qex>o'erwhelm</qex> them.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Gaza yet stands; but all her sons are fallen,⟦br⟧
All in a moment <qex>overwhelmed</qex> and fallen.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To project or impend over threateningly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His louering brows <qex>o'erwhelming</qex> his fair sight.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To cause to surround, to cover.</def>
<rj><au>Papin.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overwhelm</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Overwhelm
<hw>O"ver*whelm`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of overwhelming.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>overwhelmed</ent>⟦br⟧
